een perception and mnemonic reference in contemporary art. De Baca offers an insider’s view of the artist’s unstinting efforts to realize her artistic vision, as well as the cultural, political, and historical resonances her oeuvre has for us today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSculpture, Americany20th century. 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh  a1960s sculptor.  a20th century artists.  aamerican artists.  aamerican sculptors.  aanne truitt first.  aanne truitt hardcastle.  aanne truitt valley forge.  aanne truitt.  aart criticism.  aart history.  aartists.  acontemporary artists.  ahardcastle.  amemory studies.  amemory.  amid century minimalism.  aminimal artist.  aminimalism.  aminimalist art.  aminimalist sculptor.  aperception and mnemonic reference.  aproduction of memory.  atruitts sculptures.  avisual artist.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028661040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096297240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520962972423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520962972/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY